Directory of instances of a class or classes of real-world phenomena containing some information regarding position. Example: a gazetteer of streets in a municipality" NOTE: There may be several different gazetteers for the same location type; with the location instances represented in different ways.

Identifiable place in the real world EXAMPLE: 'Eiffel tower', 'Madrid', 'California'
Represents an instance of each location type in a spatial referencing system that is recorded in a gazetteer.

Class of places in the real world. Examples : street, junction between two streets, building, country A spatial referencing system using geographic identifiers shall comprise one or more location types (which may be related, for example by nesting), with a common theme. Each location type shall be uniquely identified by means of one or more geographic identifier types.
Structured collection of location types together with their corresponding geographic identifiers, for identifying position in the real world.
